-- Gome Says Agreement on Haier Products May Generate $7.4 Billion in Sales
-- Wendy Leung
-- 2010-07-02T07:31:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-02/gome-says-agreement-on-haier-products-may-generate-7-4-billion-in-sales.html

          
          
             Gome Electrical Appliances Holding
Ltd. , China’s second-biggest electronics retailer by market
value, will sell  Haier Group  products in a deal it says may
generate 50 billion yuan ($7.4 billion) in sales over three
years.  
 Gome will add 600 Haier products a year for distribution
in the next three years, the retailer said in an e-mailed-
statement. Half the items on sale will be exclusive to the
electronics chain, according to the statement.  
 Shares in Gome rose as much as 4.6 percent to HK$2.49
and traded at HK$2.44 at 3:17 p.m. in Hong Kong. Haier is the
world’s biggest maker of refrigerators and washing machines
by volume.  
